Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.15,0:00:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty years ago, in 1978,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.48,0:00:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the Computer Department
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.28,0:00:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,was formed in the United States.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.57,0:00:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Now overseen by the Coordinators’ Committee,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.32,0:00:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the Computer Department at headquarters
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.53,0:00:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,supports many organizational initiatives
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.66,0:00:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Governing Body and its committees.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.37,0:00:21.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It also provides global technical standards
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.17,0:00:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and unified software to all branches.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.84,0:00:27.55,Default,,0,0,0,,One such example of this software
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.55,0:00:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,is a program called HuB.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.01,0:00:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,HuB is the replacement software for Admin.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.30,0:00:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,However, replacing a program as extensive
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.31,0:00:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and critical as Admin is no small task.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.23,0:00:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what does it take?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.86,0:00:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the Coordinators’ Committee is pleased
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.11,0:00:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to share with you\Nthe following seven-minute video,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.82,0:00:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,which provides just a glimpse
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.99,0:00:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,into what is involved in the making of HuB.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.58,0:01:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Virtually every department at Bethel
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.12,0:01:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,is using a new computer program called HuB;
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.88,0:01:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it replaces Admin,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.96,0:01:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the program previously tasked
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.21,0:01:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,with being the backbone\Nin organizing nearly every aspect of Bethel work.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.22,0:01:17.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Building and transitioning to this new program
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.22,0:01:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,would be the largest project\Nthe Computer Department had ever undertaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.94,0:01:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The Admin program\Nreally grew from small beginnings
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.27,0:01:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to a program that today
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.48,0:01:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is used by almost every department in Bethel.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.74,0:01:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It was custom-designed,\Nessentially, for the organization’s needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.20,0:01:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we’ve reached a point,\Nafter these 20 years, where it’s based
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.24,0:01:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,on software that now we understand
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.25,0:01:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is no longer going to be supported\Nby the company that produced it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.29,0:01:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,There were about 9,000\Ndifferent custom forms and reports
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.34,0:01:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that had been built into Admin.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.34,0:01:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Four and a half million lines\Nof code already existed,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.93,0:01:55.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and so now we\Nhad to take all of that and convert it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.93,0:01:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s like a building with 9,000 rooms
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.76,0:02:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have to rebuild\Nand take a fresh look at from the ground up,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.77,0:02:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,‘How are we going to do this\Nusing a new set of technology?’
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.77,0:02:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This was huge; this was their Warwick project.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.49,0:02:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Where we are today,\Nwe have this replacement program called HuB.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.03,0:02:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time as building this new system,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.74,0:02:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we also had to support\Nthe existing Admin program.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.12,0:02:24.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Both of these systems\Nwere accessing and reading and writing
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.83,0:02:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to the same data source\Nat the same time, so it was very complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.09,0:02:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,To date, we have\Nat least 12 million lines of code,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.84,0:02:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is growing by the thousands every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.30,0:02:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,HuB, the replacement for Admin,\Nis already in full production
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.85,0:02:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,for most departments.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.89,0:02:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Many new organizational initiatives\Nrequire the development teams
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.69,0:02:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to design new features\Nor at least modify existing ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.57,0:02:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In some ways,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.07,0:02:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s like living in a house\Nwhile it’s being renovated,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.74,0:02:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,except in this case, the house\Nwill be fully replaced from the foundations up
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.74,0:03:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,without the family ever moving out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.62,0:03:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So developing a new program also meant
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.12,0:03:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,learning new programming tools\Nand new programming methods.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.63,0:03:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a little bit as if everybody\Nwas speaking Hebrew,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.42,0:03:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and now we had to get them all\Nto learn how to speak Greek.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.84,0:03:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve had brothers and sisters\Nthroughout the earth, actually,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.01,0:03:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,pouring their heart into this project.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.39,0:03:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We have 15 different development teams,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.02,0:03:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and they’re based in eight different branches\Nin different locations around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.81,0:03:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re also assisted by many remote volunteers
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.40,0:03:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in the field also spread out around the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.57,0:03:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So, obviously, coordinating this global group
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.65,0:03:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,has required us as a department\Nto adopt new methodologies
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.82,0:03:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,—new ways of working—\Nin order for it to be a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.70,0:03:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We get our direction\Nfrom the Governing Body committees
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.33,0:03:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and the world headquarters departments.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.33,0:03:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,They essentially come to us\Nand tell us what features need to be built,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.34,0:03:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and they also tell us when\N—or the priority as to what should come first.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.18,0:04:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The direction received
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.18,0:04:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,is translated into a format\Nused by the developers
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.18,0:04:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to write the computer code.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.93,0:04:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to document\Nthe technical requirements
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.73,0:04:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,so that a developer\Nwill know what needs to be coded.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.48,0:04:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of thought goes into the design
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.99,0:04:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of the screens before development begins,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.49,0:04:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is important so that the many\NHuB development teams around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.78,0:04:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,can be working\Non the same software project at the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.87,0:04:30.83,Default,,0,0,0,,giving the user a consistent experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.63,0:04:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.63,0:04:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,branches had to perform their own updates,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.75,0:04:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes working off compact discs\Nthat had to be sent through the mail.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.93,0:04:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,This could take weeks of work.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.14,0:04:44.35,Default,,0,0,0,,For this reason, significant updates
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.35,0:04:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,would generally happen only every six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.97,0:04:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, updating HuB
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.98,0:04:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,in all branches for all users
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.48,0:04:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,can happen several times a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.19,0:04:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We built a pipeline,\Na virtual pipeline, that allows us
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.32,0:05:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,(every time we have code ready)
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.15,0:05:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to ship, basically, the product
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.37,0:05:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,from world headquarters\Nto the branches through the network.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.29,0:05:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time code is added or edited,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.21,0:05:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the entire project\Nis automatically rebuilt and tested.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.42,0:05:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything has to be just right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.42,0:05:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,We have millions of lines of code behind this,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.92,0:05:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,so every time we add a new line\Nor we modify a line of code,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.14,0:05:26.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we need to reinspect everything
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.60,0:05:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and make sure that,\Nin an automated manner, it will still work.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.27,0:05:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,HuB is already providing new features\Nthat are assisting global initiatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.32,0:05:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,As the number\Nof translated languages for our publications
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.36,0:05:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,grows by leaps and bounds,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.49,0:05:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,so do the number of different items we print.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.99,0:05:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Branches need to know\Nwhen each new item is going to be printed
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.08,0:05:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and which branch will print it for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.25,0:05:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In the past, this required hundreds\Nof pieces of correspondence every month.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.17,0:06:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,With HuB,\Nall this information gathering is simplified.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.80,0:06:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Branches enter their information
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.51,0:06:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,directly into HuB, where it is processed,\Norganized, and shared worldwide.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.56,0:06:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,This saves countless hours of work,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.39,0:06:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,improves the accuracy of the data,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.77,0:06:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and results in a quicker response\Nto the current needs of the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.94,0:06:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Globally, the organization\Ncares for many properties.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.57,0:06:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Branches enter the location, size,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.07,0:06:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,use, or condition of each property into HuB.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.53,0:06:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s forwarded\Nto world headquarters on a weekly basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.54,0:06:34.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The HuB data can be exported and viewed
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.83,0:06:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,as tables, charts, or maps,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.58,0:06:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,showing trends that may be developing
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.09,0:06:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,for the best use of existing facilities\Nand planning for future growth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.68,0:06:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The perceived need\Nfor several thousand new Kingdom Halls
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.97,0:06:51.14,Default,,0,0,0,,was resolved by making better use
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.14,0:06:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of existing properties.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.31,0:06:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,A project of this magnitude
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.98,0:06:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,is not without its growing pains.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.27,0:07:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a little challenging,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.28,0:07:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,but I wanted to learn how to use it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.40,0:07:06.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked for the positives;\NI looked for the benefits of the program.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.91,0:07:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s easy to find what you want
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.28,0:07:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the training that they have.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.91,0:07:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,They have all kinds of references for us\Nto find the information we need
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.75,0:07:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to do our work.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.75,0:07:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Globally, over 14,000 users
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.63,0:07:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,have already received live instructor-led training.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.34,0:07:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We encourage all those who use HuB
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.68,0:07:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,to work with those within their department\Nwho provide training and support
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.26,0:07:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,because we work\Nwith those individuals to give them updates
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.18,0:07:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,as to what’s new and how to use the product.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.73,0:07:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re very thankful to the brothers and sisters
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.02,0:07:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,who have taken the time to learn this program.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.98,0:07:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We realize that it’s a work in progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.99,0:07:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a work in progress for them and a work\Nin progress for us who are developing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.49,0:07:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We value their feedback,\Nand we want to use that feedback
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.78,0:07:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to try and improve the program together.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.79,0:07:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,At Exodus 36:1,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.58,0:08:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,we read how Bezalel worked along with Oholiab,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.67,0:08:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to whom Jehovah had given\N“wisdom and understanding,” allowing them
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.26,0:08:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,to accomplish work to his praise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.22,0:08:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In a similar way,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.30,0:08:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,projects like this can be daunting\N—even overwhelming—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.89,0:08:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet Jehovah’s spirit enables our success.
